text: I think the cards for the precons also remove the Standard and Limited restrictions so development and design are more free to explore.
They still leave plenty of room for finding unintended interactions. Sam’s worry is a bit overstated.
Precons are a gateway into the format. I’m not quite on board with Mr Black’s position here
There are too many cards at this point to know every, or even most, interactions etc. That’s part of the creative discovery.
Biggest problem with precons is usually the power level of the commanders
That aspect is a bit centralizing
Precons give us 5 Merens for every 1 Narset standard gives us
Also, why can’t EDH have nice things of our own?

A criticism I will throw the precon’s way is related to that power level, I think. Ur-Dragon is kind of “the” dragon Commander. Atraxa is “the” superfriends general. They can be contested by later designs, but if you want to build a theme, it’s hard not to pick the precon guy that embodies that theme so fully
The most obvious yes I see that, but as you progress in the game and your own deckbuilding, very often you don’t want the ‘best’ but branch out to try more subtle interactions.
The best overall rarely feeds most theme decks, which are a large part of EDH.

I think it will be less of a problem going forward. They’re no longer building to constraints of a color pie, but dedicating time to exploring a theme. Say they did a UR artifact deck for one of the future products. There are tons of directions they can take a concept that vague. So we might see less of the “this is the obvious choice” commanders like we do with Atraxa
I think also the four color were a bit of an aberration given the difficulty inherent in that particular design space.
Very true assessment. They did great work on them, even if Atraxa stepped over the power level line
She’s powerful but I’m not sure I agree about stepping over.
But that’s purely personal.
Yeah, I think Atraxa is fine. Good but fine.
Breya and Ydris are stronger, and maybe Saskia too
Breya and Yidris are combo engines. Not sure I agree about Saskia, though. She’s very powerful but Atraxa’s in better colors and individually stronger.
Poor K&T...
They just like dancing by themselves....
Honesty K&T are in very good Stax colors...
You can make very nasty K&T decks.

K&T embody the spirit of blackless very impressively. Proliferation is a fantastic gradual redless word. Nonblue is aggressive, non green is metal that can become anything at all, overall very elegant work 

I actually disagree there don—I bet the intent was initially to have them be partners, but the fact that they’re a single inseparable unit is very moving
I just think its confusing at the start when it was k&t and tymna & tana etc
